   {:e #blake3 "1dc9483a7ef8df7041bfacf8bfc23d81723a1942b689f247b9c3f452f86972bb" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Two related performance defects in concept.rs. DEFECT-007: concept_inventory scans all datoms TWICE — once for :concept/name, once for remaining attributes. DEFECT-015: format_concept_status calls is_innate() per concept, and is_innate does a full datom scan. With 25 concepts and 88K datoms: 2*88K + 25*88K = 2.4M iterations on every braid status. APPROACH: (1) Rewrite concept_inventory as single-pass: one loop over store.datoms(), check attribute against all concept-related attributes. Insert-or-update in the BTreeMap. Also collect :concept/innate into a HashSet<EntityId> during the same pass. (2) Change format_concept_status to accept the innate set as parameter (or return it from concept_inventory). Replace is_innate(store, entity) calls with innate_set.contains(&entity). (3) This changes concept_inventory return type or adds a companion function. ACCEPTANCE: (A) concept_inventory makes exactly 1 pass over store.datoms() (verify by counting iterations or by code inspection). (B) format_concept_status makes 0 additional datom scans beyond calling concept_inventory. (C) All existing concept tests pass. (D) New benchmark: format_concept_status with 100K datoms and 20 concepts completes in < 10ms. DEPENDS-ON: nothing (orthogonal to correctness fixes). FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs:249-318, 719-767" :op :assert}
